On June 20, 2023, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. announced that the national emergency declared on July 14, 2020, with respect to the situation in Hong Kong will continue for another year. The declaration was made in response to the unusual and extraordinary threat posed by recent actions taken by the People's Republic of China to undermine Hong Kong's autonomy. The national emergency is deemed necessary to protect the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States. This announcement will be published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress.